---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Occupational Therapists | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Occupational Therapists working internationally, covering OT careers abroad, rehabilitation positions, and global healthcare opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Occupational Therapists";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Occupational Therapists working abroad, providing rehabilitation internationally, and pursuing careers across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare organizations worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/occupational-therapist-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/occupational-therapist-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Occupational Therapist Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Occupational Therapists help people develop, recover, and maintain skills needed for daily living and working. International OT careers offer opportunities to work with diverse populations, experience different healthcare approaches, and contribute to rehabilitation and wellness in various cultural contexts.
      </p>
      <p>
        International OT opportunities exist through hospitals and rehabilitation centers worldwide, international schools, humanitarian organizations, and countries actively recruiting allied health professionals to address growing rehabilitation needs.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Occupational Therapists working abroad across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare organizations worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Occupational Therapists</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Physical injury coverage', why: 'Patient handling and transfers', typical: 'Important for profession' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Treatment positioning', typical: 'Consider for long-term' },
          { need: 'Professional liability', why: 'Treatment liability', typical: 'Verify provision' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Patient care demands', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Disability coverage', why: 'Physical career aspects', typical: 'Review carefully' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Physical Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Occupational therapy involves physical work—patient transfers, activity demonstration, and hands-on treatment. These demands create musculoskeletal injury risks. Physical injury coverage is important for sustaining OT careers.
      </p>
      <p>
        Some OT settings involve more physical work than others. Acute care and rehabilitation settings typically have higher physical demands than outpatient or mental health practice.
      </p>

      <h3>Emotional Investment</h3>
      <p>
        OTs develop therapeutic relationships with patients through ongoing treatment. Working with patients facing disability or chronic conditions creates emotional demands. Mental health support helps sustain long-term careers in rehabilitation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Hospitals</h3>
      <p>
        Acute and rehabilitation hospitals. Hospital benefits comprehensive. Varied caseloads. Hospitals offer resources.
      </p>

      <h3>Outpatient Clinics</h3>
      <p>
        Rehabilitation clinics. Clinic benefits variable. Community-based. Clinics offer consistency.
      </p>

      <h3>Schools</h3>
      <p>
        School-based OT. School or agency benefits. Pediatric focus. Schools offer schedules.
      </p>

      <h3>Home Health</h3>
      <p>
        Home-based treatment. Agency benefits. Community setting. Home health offers flexibility.
      </p>

      <h3>Mental Health</h3>
      <p>
        Psychiatric OT settings. Facility benefits. Mental health focus. MH settings offer specialization.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Occupational Therapists"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Occupational Therapists working abroad across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare organizations worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare OT Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>OT Degree</h3>
      <p>
        Masters or doctorate in OT. Professional degree. Foundation credential. Degree enables licensure.
      </p>

      <h3>Licensure</h3>
      <p>
        Home country registration. OTR credential in US. National certification. Licensure enables practice.
      </p>

      <h3>International Recognition</h3>
      <p>
        Recognition varies by country. WFOT standards exist. May need additional credentials. Research destination.
      </p>

      <h3>Specialty Certification</h3>
      <p>
        Hand therapy, pediatrics, etc. Advanced credentials. Specialization focus. Certifications enhance career.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Physical Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Patient transfers. Activity demonstration. Hands-on treatment. Physical coverage important.
      </p>

      <h3>Emotional</h3>
      <p>
        Patient relationships. Disability adjustment. Family dynamics. Mental health support valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Ergonomic</h3>
      <p>
        Treatment positioning. Equipment use. Sustained postures. Ergonomic coverage valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Documentation</h3>
      <p>
        Extensive documentation. Computer work. Administrative demands. Ergonomic consideration.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Assessment</h3>
      <p>
        Functional evaluation. Activity analysis. Goal setting. Assessment guides treatment.
      </p>

      <h3>Treatment</h3>
      <p>
        Therapeutic activities. Skill development. Adaptation training. Treatment builds independence.
      </p>

      <h3>Documentation</h3>
      <p>
        Progress notes. Insurance documentation. Outcome measurement. Documentation supports care.
      </p>

      <h3>Collaboration</h3>
      <p>
        Healthcare team coordination. Family involvement. Discharge planning. Collaboration ensures comprehensive care.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Global Demand</h3>
      <p>
        OT shortage in many countries. Aging populations increasing need. Active recruitment. Opportunities exist.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Staff OT to senior. Clinical specialist. Manager. Educator. Multiple paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>License Portability</h3>
      <p>
        WFOT helps portability. Still varies by country. May need additional credentials. Research destination.
      </p>

      <h3>Work-Life Balance</h3>
      <p>
        Generally reasonable hours. Some settings demanding. School settings offer schedules. Balance achievable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm an OT considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Credential recognition varies. Hospital positions typically offer coverage. WFOT helps portability. Research specific destination.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do international healthcare facilities provide coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Hospital positions typically yes. Clinics variable. International schools often provide. Verify before accepting.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is physical injury coverage important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for rehabilitation work. Patient handling demands. Back injuries common. Consider physical coverage.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Can I practice with my home country credential?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Depends on destination. WFOT recognition helps. Often additional requirements. Research specific country.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is mental health support valuable?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for patient care demands. Emotional investment in patients. Rehabilitation challenges. Support valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Strong global demand. Aging populations driving need. Shortages in many countries. Positive opportunities.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by researching credential recognition in your target destination. Verify physical injury coverage for rehabilitation work. Consider mental health support for patient care demands. Check WFOT resources for international practice guidance.
      </p>
      <p>
        Occupational Therapists help people live fully worldwide. Your coverage should support rehabilitation careers—addressing physical demands, protecting against injury, and maintaining your health across OT positions worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your OT Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Occupational Therapists working abroad across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare organizations worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
